MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the per-trial set_wall + zobrist + DirMasks-rebuild BFS with a
speculative bitboard pipeline (path::parallel):

- WallGrids: four directional blocked-step u128 masks in the centered
  11-stride flood layout; a wall trial is a mask flip (place/remove of a
  precomputed const delta), no board mutation.
- Linear flood fill: one-step parallel dilation in all four directions per
  iteration, early exit on goal contact or stagnation.
- Bit theft: P2's flood annexes P1's cached visited region on first contact
  (pawn connectivity is undirected), goal-testing the annexed pool
  immediately.

Fixes two V10 movegen soundness bugs:

1. False negatives: both_players_reach_goals_with_masks concluded from P1's
   *partial* early-exit component that P2 was trapped (empty board with
   P1(7,4)/P2(6,4) returned false). Replaced the shortcut with a seeded
   bit-theft flood. Three replay tests had asserted these false negatives
   as expected behavior (a5h ply14, g1v, a6h) — naive can_step BFS confirms
   all three walls keep both goal paths open; tests updated and the full
   external replay test re-enabled.
2. False positives: can_wall_block_topology compared the H-wall right edge
   against js_col == 9, unreachable for 0-based slots, so right-edge H walls
   skipped the path check and trapping walls were accepted. This was the
   canta oracle perft mismatch (game 0 depth 2: 5980 != 5978); all 15 canta
   games now match at depths 1-3.

Perf (release, perft): canta midgames d3 4.35 -> 24.14 Mnodes/s (5.5x),
startpos d4 83.3 -> 150.6 Mnodes/s (1.8x).
